[Weekly Briefing] Nurburgring Nordschleife - 2016s3 Week 7
[size=18][i][b]Welcome to the SRF![/b][/size]
We pride ourselves on a friendly, competitive and yet relaxed atmosphere both on and off-track. Don't be afraid to ask for help, either in practice sessions or on the forum![/i]

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2429680.page[/img]

[color=red][size=18]Spec Racer Ford Challenge Series @ [b] Nordschleife Industriefahrten [/b]
Week 7 of 12 - 2016 Season 3[/size][/color]
Race Distance: 3 laps, approximately 25-30 minutes


This week we travel to the famous 'Green Hell' - Nurburgring Nordschleife. This is the touristfarhten layout - i.e. NOT including the GP track. This is a long and technical track, which can be intimidating without practise. However, the long track can make for some epic racing battles.

[size=18][b]IMPORTANT NOTES FOR THIS WEEK[/b][/size]
Unlike normal weeks the following are in effect:
	- Separate qualifying in which you get [b][i]ONE (1)[/b][/i] timed lap, starting from the tourist entrance. Sessions run hourly.
	- Static weather. Every session will have the same weather condidions! Likely to be 80F, 2mph @W wind, 40RH, partly cloudy (TBC).

