[size=18][b]TRACK NOTES[/b][/size]

There are many 'driving guides' for the Nordschleife available online, and plenty of great info, fast lap replays etc. in last season's thread, which you can find here: http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/list/3479409.page
BMW made an easy-to-digest guide, available here: http://www.billzilla.org/bmwring.pdf
I wrote an SRF-specific guide to help remember the later half of the lap here: https://gist.github.com/pwallington/7ec44ed5e9422ebf4b8a17530db6d92c


Regardless, some important notes:
       - There are not many overtaking opportunities early on in the lap - especially on lap 1, BE PATIENT and you will have plenty of chances later on.
       - The SRF really doesn't like the kerbs, especially on the exits of corners - be careful!
       - The relatively low power of the SRF makes many of the faster corners easy flat-out or only a small lift.

Daniil has posted a very safe and easy-to-drive setup [url=http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/list/200/3349192.page#9443179]HERE[/url] (updated version also attached to this post). It understeers quite a lot, but it is easy to drive fast and is friendlier over the kerbs than the baseline. The current world record SRF laptime was run with this setup!

