Rob Adams' detailed track guide to the Nordschleife: 

After the start line, you wiggle a few times before a long straight. The only corner that matters is the one before the long straight. If you try to go fast on the others, at least you haven't wasted much time and you can start again from the pits. 

The next section is long and flat out except where it isn't. The places where it isn't will kill you. 

Then you go downhill for a while. The downhill is easy and fast except where it isn't. The place where it isn't easy and fast will kill you. 

Eventually you cross a bridge. After that bridge, you go flat out for a long time, except for one place where you don't. That place will kill you. It's also dark. And scary. I think there are monsters there. 

After a long flat out run, you get to a carousel. If you get it right, it's the best thing ever. You will never get it right. 

The rest of the track is a mystery. You go up, you go down. Corners will come up when you least expect them. If you go too fast, they will kill you. If you go too slow, you will feel like a coward. I think some of the corners move around between laps. 

Eventually the track straightens out. If you got the entry to the straight right, you'll be happy. Otherwise you have a minute or so to realize that your lap time is going to suck and you just wasted 8 minutes.